    "created_at": "2017-06-08T17:39:10Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-06-08T17:39:10Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Wait what.\r\n\r\n>Requiring armaments to have unique names is a design feature, and the difference between Single vs First is going to be negligible in these cases.\r\n\r\nI have a visual effect I dubbed as electrolaser. It's achieved via firing a laser and a teslabolt armament at the same time, with exactly the same settings (armament name, effect duration, reloaddelay) to make sure they will stay in sync with each other.\r\n\r\nAlso TS/RA2's eliteweapon set-up also imply their OpenRA equvivalents should share the armament names.\r\n\r\nPlease explain to me why cases like these should have different armament names."
  },
